<paragraph id="IAS01_98" base="F3903607" principles="no"><paranum>98</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IASÂ 1"/><data name="paranum" value="98"/></prolog><body><p id="IAS01_P0516" outputclass="keep_with_next">Circumstances that would give rise to the separate disclosure of items of income and expense include:</p><ol id="IAS01_L0055" base="F3903609" type="lower-alpha"><li id="IAS01_98_a"><li_value>(a)</li_value>         <p id="IAS01_P0517" base="F3903610">write&#x2011;downs of inventories to net realisable value or of property, plant and equipment to recoverable amount, as well as reversals of such write&#x2011;downs;</p>       </li><li id="IAS01_98_b"><li_value>(b)</li_value>         <p id="IAS01_P0518" base="F3903612">restructurings of the activities of an entity and reversals of any provisions for the costs of restructuring;</p>       </li><li id="IAS01_98_c"><li_value>(c)</li_value>         <p id="IAS01_P0519" base="F3903614">disposals of items of property, plant and equipment;</p>       </li><li id="IAS01_98_d"><li_value>(d)</li_value>         <p id="IAS01_P0520" base="F3903616">disposals of investments;</p>       </li><li id="IAS01_98_e"><li_value>(e)</li_value>         <p id="IAS01_P0521" base="F3903618">discontinued operations;</p>       </li><li id="IAS01_98_f"><li_value>(f)</li_value>         <p id="IAS01_P0522" base="F3903620">litigation settlements; and</p>       </li><li id="IAS01_98_g"><li_value>(g)</li_value>         <p id="IAS01_P0523" base="F3903622">other reversals of provisions.</p>       </li></ol></body></paragraph>